eclipse-v0.2.16 
--------------------------

Patch Notes:

Barely any change. Updated the verbiage in "How to Play"

eclipse-v0.2.15 
--------------------------

Patch Notes:

Fix network freeze bug caused by receive("*a") overwhelming server thread:

  - Changed network receive calls from reading all available data at once to reading in 4KB 
  chunks, which prevents the server thread from locking up during high network traffic. 
  
  - Added buffer size limits and improved error handling to ensure stable performance during 
  gameplay. 
  
  - This resolves the issue where the game would freeze during online multiplayer due
   to inefficient message processing.


eclipse-v0.2.14 
--------------------------

Patch Notes:

1) Fixed network freeze bug caused by message fragmentation in server thread:

 - The server was using line-mode receive() without buffering, causing partial messages to be
 lost when TCP packets were fragmented. This led to desynchronization between clients and
 the server, resulting in gameplay freezes.
  
 - Added proper message buffering to the server thread matching the client's implementation, ensuring all fragmented messages are correctly
 reassembled.

2) Added data validation to the load save file function(s)

eclipse-v0.2.13 
--------------------------

Patch Notes:

- Added a turn counter
 - Single Player: Counts the number of turns the player (Player 1/Light) has taken.
 - Multiplayer (Online mode): Counts the number of turns from the perspective of each player separately

Fixed play again freeze bug in online multiplayer

- Removed the surrender button from single player mode

